Code is the poetry of logic.
In the garden of algorithms, every loop blooms.
Bugs are just features in disguise.
The best error message is no error at all.
Simplicity is the ultimate sophistication.
Comments explain what, code explains how.
A function should do one thing, and do it well.
Build for the user you want to be, not the user you are.
Every abstraction is a lie that tells the truth.
The hard part is not writing code, it's writing code that lasts.